My pathplanner auto should follow a path containing a marker in which the arm moves to prepare to shoot with ArmSmartGoTo. Subsequently, after the path ends, it should shoot with AutoShootCycle. However, the auto moves to the path’s starting point, then ArmSmartGoTo runs, but the auto never follows the actual path and never runs AutoShootCycle.

It looks like your directory structure is wrong. Mostly likely scenario is that you opened pathplanner in the wrong directory when you first started making things, and you’re not actually loading the paths you think you’re loading.

Your autos and paths should be in a directory named pathplanner, in a directory named deploy. For example:
deploy\pathplanner\autos\Test auto.auto references a path named Command Testing…but
deploy\pathplanner\paths\ has about 13-15 paths in there, none of them named Command Testing.path.

If you want to see a working Python Pathplanner setup, ours works. Fully supports simulation if you want to mess around with it. I make no claim that what we do is optimal…but it is definitely functional.
